{"key":"post-8567165","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8567165</id>\n<content>We use the veil tearing as a good indicator of when to pick, but there's no 'magic time' that you must pick.&amp;nbsp; Unless you're making spore prints, you don't want to let them go much past the veil tearing since they'll make a mess and taste horrible.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If they're in the large pin size, they're okay to pick.&amp;nbsp; In my experience, that's when quality is highest, even though you get less total product.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8567170</next>\n<prev>8567156</prev>\n<first>8567118</first>\n<last>8567902</last>\n<when>1214513708</when>\n<utime>06/26/08 11:55 PM</utime>\n</post>"}